SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [flag . . .] file -locurses [library . . .]

       #include <ocurses.h>

       int beep(void); int flash(void);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  beep and flash routines are used to signal the termi-
       nal user.  The routine beep sounds the  audible  alarm  on
       the  terminal,  if  possible;  if that is not possible, it
       flashes the screen (visible bell), if  that  is  possible.
       The  routine  flash flashes the screen, and if that is not
       possible, sounds the audible signal.  If neither signal is
       possible,  nothing  happens.  Nearly all terminals have an
       audible signal (bell or beep), but only some can flash the
       screen.

   RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       These routines always return OK.

